<!-- DRAFT: have a qualified attorney review before launch -->
<Prose
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="What Styled by Susanne collects today (the booking questionnaire), what changes when the email list and analytics go live, how it's used, and how to ask for deletion."
  eyebrow="Policies"
  intro="What I collect, why, and the promise underneath it all: your information is never for sale."
  dateline="Draft, last updated July 18, 2026"
>
  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>
    I collect only what I need to reply to you and do good work, I use it only
    for the reasons you gave it to me, I never sell it, and if you ever want
    something deleted, you just have to ask.
  </p>

  <h2>What I collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>The booking questionnaire.</strong> When you book a style
      conversation, the form (currently run through Google Forms) asks for
      your name, contact details, and answers about your closet, lifestyle,
      and style goals.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Email signup.</strong> When the studio email list goes live,
      signing up shares your email address so I can send you the guide and
      newsletter you asked for.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Basic analytics.</strong> When analytics are enabled, I&rsquo;ll
      see aggregate information about how the site is used: which pages are
      visited and where visitors come from. I use it to make the site better,
      not to identify individual people.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How I use it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Replying to your inquiry and having the style conversation.</li>
    <li>Providing the styling services you book.</li>
    <li>Sending the newsletter and free resources you signed up for.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    That&rsquo;s it. I don&rsquo;t sell your information, rent it, trade it,
    or hand it to advertisers. Ever.
  </p>

  <h2>Third parties involved</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Forms</strong> processes the booking questionnaire, so
      Google&rsquo;s own privacy policy applies to that form.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>An email provider</strong> (still being chosen) will store the
      email list once it&rsquo;s live. I&rsquo;ll name the provider here when
      it&rsquo;s selected.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Affiliate networks.</strong> When you click a shoppable link,
      retailers and networks like Amazon and Mavely may set their own cookies
      on <em>their</em> sites to track the purchase. Those cookies live on
      their sites, under their privacy policies; I don&rsquo;t control them.
      More in the
      <a href="/policies/affiliate-disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Client photos and stories</h2>
  <p>
    Your closet is private. Nothing from an engagement (photos, before and
    afters, quotes, or any detail of your story) is ever shared publicly
    without your written permission first. No permission, no post. Simple.
  </p>

  <h2>Deletion and questions</h2>
  <p>
    Want your questionnaire answers, email address, or anything else deleted?
    Email me and I&rsquo;ll take care of it and confirm when it&rsquo;s done.
    The same address works for any privacy question.
  </p>

  <h2>An honest note</h2>
  <p>
    This policy is a plain-English draft written to tell you the truth about
    how the site works today. A formal legal review is pending before launch,
    and this page will be updated if anything changes, but the commitments
    above stand either way.
  </p>

  <p>
    Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
  </p>
</Prose>
